nodeInput.text:
openapi: 3.0.0
servers:
- description: SwaggerHub API Auto Mocking
  url: https://virtserver.swaggerhub.com/ericryanbowser/AssistApi/1.0.0
- description: HTTPs
  url: https://localhost:3001
info:
  description: Node.js Assistant API with Vectors
  version: 1.0.0
  title: Node Assist API
  contact:
    email: ericryanbowser@gmail.com
  license:
    name: MIT
paths:
  /askAssist:
    post:
      summary: Text Question
      operationId: assist
      description: Ask assistant a question
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Returns an answer
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
        '400':
          description: bad request
      parameters:
      - name: content
        in: query
        description: Question to ask
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string

# Assist Node.js Back-end
API for personal assistant using openai

# Front-end using React.js, Webpack, Boostrap, and Axios for API requests
  - Simple interface for `openai` API: https://www.npmjs.com/package/openai

# This API takes chat completion requests and image generation requests for right now
1. Completion and Code Extraction
2. Image generation
3. Embeddings and documents
    - Use postgreSQL for storing a thread conversation
    - Save the embedding tokens for future access or just threads
5. Agents or swarm APIs (not sure yet)

version: '3'
services:
  frontend:
    build: ./frontend
    ports:
      - "80:80"
  backend:
    build: ./backend
    ports:
      - "3000:3000"
